  "model_assumptions": {
    "capacity_vs_contracts": "Phase 2 public system capacity is at least 5 MtCO2/y, while the five named public agreements sum to about 2.88 MtCO2/y; remaining capacity is represented as unallocated open-access capacity, not as a sixth emitter.",
    "vessel_capacity_t": "The 7,500 m3 vessels use the existing model value of 8,000 t. The 12,000 m3 vessels are converted with the same t/m3 ratio, giving 12,800 t.",
    "vessel_assignment": "Connections are service eligibility for a pooled fleet, not fixed one-vessel-one-emitter routes.",
    "terminal_storage_capacity_t": "Set to four 8,000 t cargo equivalents for Phase 2 operations because exact expanded tank capacity was not found in reviewed public sources.",
    "berth_count": "Set to 2 to represent the public Phase 2 new-jetty expansion item.",
    "well_capacity": "This visualization scenario uses only the two current public well locations. Each is assigned 300 t/h so the pair can cover the 5 Mt/y system flow of 570.8 t/h for high-level operations display. This is a modelling allocation, not a public single-well rating.",
    "phase2_new_well_names_and_coordinates": "Public sources reviewed state two new offshore injection wells but do not provide confirmed names or coordinates, so they are not instantiated in this scenario.",
    "well_coordinates": "A7 AH and C1 H coordinates are carried over from the Phase 1 physical-layer data and documentation in this repository. Phase 2 new well locations are intentionally not added.",
    "emitter_coordinates": "Each emitter is represented by one aggregate coordinate. Orsted uses the Kalundborg Hub aggregate point at Asnaes Power Station rather than splitting Asnaes and Avedore. Coordinates are suitable for scenario routing/topology, not for facility-boundary or jetty-level engineering."
  },
